HEADWORD: Trikosane
<hw>Tri"ko*sane</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>tri-</ets> + Gr. <?/ twenty.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
hydrocarbon, <chform>C23H48</chform>, of the methane series, resembling
paraffin; -- so called because it has <xex>twenty-three</xex> atoms of
carbon in the molecule.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trilateral</ent>⟦br⟧
